5. triumphali lauro: 1, 7, 5-8 n. The laurel crown on the Apollo of Skopas was evidently meant to suggest the song of triumph after the fight with the Titans to which Tibullus himself alludes in 9-10. The fight with the Titans is throughout the divine prototypa and analogy of the fight with the Lords of Misrule at Actium. When, therefore, the Apollo of Skopas be- carne the Apollo of the Palatine, the laurel crown symbolized the triumph at Actium as well as its Olympian prototype. -temporar 1, 1, 70 11.
